	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Cape Town - United States President Donald Trump spoke by
phone on Monday with his Nigerian counterpart President Muhammadu Buhari. In a statement Buhari's spokesperson Femi Adesina described the
conversation between the two leaders as "cordial". See some of the contents from the statement below - according to BBC. "The conversation was cordial and President Buhari
congratulated Trump on his election as President of the United States, and on
his cabinet.         According to New York Times, the conversation took place, as
Buhari's countrymen wondered where their president was, having not heard from
him in weeks. Buhari, 74, left Nigeria for a vacation on January 19, which
he later extended on February 5 for medical tests and treatment in London. His
aides have, however, refused to give details about his health and his whereabouts,
the report said. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  